# AGENTS

## Overview

- App: `{{.AppName}}`
- Module: `{{.ModulePath}}`
- Primary config file: `{{.AppName}}-config.toml`
- CLI support is always enabled.

## Enabled Features

| Feature | Status |
|---------|--------|
| CLI | enabled |
| API | {{if .Features.API}}enabled{{else}}disabled{{end}} |
| MCP | {{if .Features.MCP}}enabled{{else}}disabled{{end}} |
| UI | {{if .Features.UI}}enabled{{else}}disabled{{end}} |
| DB | {{if .Features.DB}}enabled ({{.DBType}}{{if .UseXDAL}}, xdal{{end}}){{else}}disabled{{end}} |
| Cache | {{if .Features.Cache}}enabled ({{.CacheType}}){{else}}disabled{{end}} |
| Docker | {{if .Features.Docker}}enabled{{else}}disabled{{end}} |
| Nomad | {{if .Features.Nomad}}enabled{{else}}disabled{{end}} |

## Project Layout

- `main.go`: CLI entrypoint.
- `cmd/`: command registration and command implementations.
- `build/`: build metadata injected through `ldflags`.
{{- if .Features.API}}
- `cmd/routes/`: HTTP route registration.
- `internal/rest/`: JSON/HTTP helpers.
- `internal/auth/`: auth middleware placeholders.
- `internal/ctxkeys/`: typed context keys.
- `internal/sample/`: sample handler -> service -> storage implementation.
{{- end}}
{{- if .Features.MCP}}
- `cmd/mcp/`: MCP server wiring and sample tool.
{{- end}}
{{- if .Features.DB}}
- `internal/db/`: connection setup and schema.
{{- if .UseXDAL}}
  The DB package returns a `Connection` wrapper with:
  `SQL` for raw `*sql.DB`
  `DB` for `xdal.DBInterface`
{{- else}}
  The DB package returns a raw `*sql.DB`.
{{- end}}
{{- end}}
{{- if and .Features.Cache (eq (toString .CacheType) "redis")}}
- `internal/redis/`: Redis client initialization.
{{- end}}
{{- if and .Features.Cache (eq (toString .CacheType) "valkey")}}
- `internal/valkey/`: Valkey client initialization.
{{- end}}
{{- if .Features.UI}}
- `web/`: frontend source, templates, Vite config, and built assets.
{{- end}}
{{- if needsSRV}}
- `internal/resolve/`: DNS SRV resolution support.
{{- end}}

## Configuration Model

- Runtime config is loaded from `{{.AppName}}-config.toml`.
- Environment variables and command flags can override config values.
- Logging config is always present under `[log]`.
{{- if .Features.API}}
- API server config lives under `[server]`.
{{- end}}
{{- if .Features.DB}}
- Database config lives under `[database]`.
{{- end}}
{{- if and .Features.Cache (eq (toString .CacheType) "redis")}}
- Cache config lives under `[redis]`.
{{- end}}
{{- if and .Features.Cache (eq (toString .CacheType) "valkey")}}
- Cache config lives under `[valkey]`.
{{- end}}

## Working Rules

- Prefer the generated task targets before inventing ad hoc build or test commands.
- Preserve the generated layering and self-registration patterns unless there is a deliberate refactor.
- Use `go-scaffolder add` for new CLI commands, API endpoints, or MCP tools when the scaffolder is available.
- Do not remove comments that start with `go-scaffolder:` unless you also update the patching flow that depends on them.
- When editing feature-specific code, keep imports and initialization aligned with the enabled feature set.

## Standard Commands

```sh
task build
task build-local
task test
task lint
```

## Feature-Specific Commands

{{- if .Features.UI}}
Frontend:

```sh
task frontend-build
```
{{- end}}

## Runtime Entry Points

```sh
go run . serve
go run . init
go run . completion --shell bash
```

{{- if .Features.DB}}
## Database Notes

- Connection setup supports direct `host:port` targets and DNS SRV names that start with `_`.
- Schema lives in `internal/db/schema.sql`.
{{- if .UseXDAL}}
- Use `conn.DB` for portable query-builder-based access.
- Use `conn.SQL` for migrations, pool configuration, or low-level SQL calls.
{{- end}}
{{- end}}

{{- if .Features.Cache}}
## Cache Notes

- Cache clients also support SRV-style names starting with `_`.
{{- end}}

{{- if .Features.UI}}
## Frontend Notes

- Vite is used for frontend builds.
- Tailwind CSS is integrated through `@tailwindcss/vite`.
- The main frontend entrypoints are `web/src/main.ts` and `web/src/style.css`.
{{- end}}

## Testing Expectations

- Run `task test` after meaningful Go changes.
- Run `task lint` before concluding changes.
{{- if .Features.UI}}
- Run `task frontend-build` after frontend dependency or asset-pipeline changes.
{{- end}}
- Generated projects are expected to pass `go test ./...` out of the box.
